headline.main: LONG WAR AHEAD, ITALIANS ARE TOLD; Mussolini's Paper Predicts a Continued Front in Russia 'After Fall of Moscow'

lead_paragraph: ROME, Oct. 16 (U.P.) -- Benito Mussolini's newspaper said today that the fall of Moscow -- which it predicted as imminent -- would not end either Russian resistance or Anglo-American hostility, and that the war probably would develop into an endurance contest.
abstract: Milan Popolo d'ltalia predicts continued USSR resistance after Moscow fall; situation discussed
